     1→# The only accessible & unstyled & full featured Input OTP component in the Web. …
     3→### OTP Input for React 🔐 by [@guilhermerodz](https://twitter.com/guilherme_rodz)
    18→https://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/753751f5-eda8-4145-a4b9-7ef51ca5e453
    19→
    20→## Usage
    22→```bash
    23→npm install input-otp
    24→```
    25→
    26→Then import the component.
    27→
    28→```diff
    29→+'use client'
    30→+import { OTPInput } from 'input-otp'
    31→
    32→function MyForm() {
    33→  return <form>
    34→+   <OTPInput maxLength={6} render={({slots})  => (...)} />
    35→  </form>
    36→}
    37→```
    38→
    39→## Default example
    41→The example below uses `tailwindcss` `@shadcn/ui` `tailwind-merge` `clsx`:
    42→
    43→```tsx
    44→'use client'
    45→import { OTPInput, SlotProps } from 'input-otp'
    46→<OTPInput
    47→  maxLength={6}
    48→  containerClassName="group flex items-center has-[:disabled]:opacity-30"
    49→  render={({ slots }) => (
    50→    <>
    51→      <div className="flex">
    52→        {slots.slice(0, 3).map((slot, idx) => (
    53→          <Slot key={idx} {...slot} />
    54→        ))}
    55→      </div>
    56→
    57→      <FakeDash />
    58→
    59→      <div className="flex">
    60→        {slots.slice(3).map((slot, idx) => (
    61→          <Slot key={idx} {...slot} />
    62→        ))}
